        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p><sic><addressee>Rev. Isaak Leeser</addressee></sic>&#44; <placeName>Phila.</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><placeName>Smyrna</placeName>&#44; <date>April 18. 1852</date></p>
			<p>Sir&#33;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Yours of the <date>14.</date> inst came duly<lb/> to hand&#44; as also did the 2 No&#58; of The<lb/> occident. Enclosed I send you Three<lb/> Dollars subscription for the ensuing year&#44;<lb/> for which you <del>pl</del> will please to send me<lb/> receipt by <sic>retourn</sic> of mail.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">When I look round and reflect&#44;<lb/> how much the christian religion &#40;and parti&#45;<lb/>cular in this country&#41; are doing to annex<lb/> Jews to her church&#44; I am indeed <sic>suprised</sic><lb/> to find you in your &#44;&#44;Jewish advocate&#34; com&#45;<lb/>plaining&#44; for not having <sic>encouragments</sic> enough<lb/> from our fellow&#45;Israelites in your different<lb/> works <del>of</del> on our holy religion. I think it<lb/> to be the duty of every true Israelite to<lb/> defend Judaism from the attacks daily made<lb/> by our opponents&#44; and believe me&#44; Rev. Sir&#44;<lb/> were it in my power to obtain more subscri&#45;<lb/>bers <del>to</del> for your valuable organ &#44;&#44;the occident&#34;<lb/> I would most assuredly do my best&#44; to get<lb/> them. I am not at all surprised that<lb/> you hadn&#39;t any <sic>subsribers</sic> before&#44; in this</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>State&#44; as there is not more than me and<lb/> another Israelite living on this <placeName>Peninsula</placeName>&#44;<lb/> and I regret to state that the latter<lb/> is married to a christian lady.&#8212;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I am&#44; Rev. Sir&#44; with <sic>greatt</sic> respect</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Yours</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Morris Stern</persName></p>
          
        </body>
